cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks for building extraction from remote sensing imagery, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper extensively evaluates four state-of-the-art CNN architectures for this task, which involves semantic pixel-wise labeling and multi-scale textural information, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed framework, which suggests a potential application in robotics (cs.RO) for autonomous navigation and mapping.
